---
title: Creamy Chickpea Salad Lettuce Wraps with Almonds
description: This 10-minute no-cook vegetarian lunch idea is light, bright, and full of flavors that will whisk you back to your tuna salad sandwich days (minus the tuna and the bread). The ever-adaptable chickpea is mashed with scallion greens, dill, fresh lemon, and a creamy powerhouse sauce of miso, mayonnaise, sour cream, mustard, and garlic. Load it into crisp lettuce cradles and sprinkle with crunchy almonds. When you’re done, you’ll be delighted to find approximately zero pans or baking sheets to wash! Now that’s a (lettuce) wrap.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/creamy-chickpea-salad-lettuce-wraps-c69e24e1.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/646465e46692a7186201d2dd.pdf
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 480 kcal
  fat: 24 g
  saturated fat: 3.5 g
  carbohydrates: 54 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 14 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 1010 mg
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
time required: 10 minutes
cuisine: North America
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/creamy-chickpea-salad-lettuce-wraps-646465e46692a7186201d2dd
---

Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @lemon{1}. Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%400g can}; pat dry with #paper towels{}.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(greens only, whites saved for another use). Pick
@dill{1/4%ounce}(fronds picked and chopped) from stems; roughly chop. Trim and
discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; separate leaves.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoons}, @sour cream{1.5%tablespoons},
@Dijon mustard{2%teaspoons}, @miso sauce concentrate{1}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon},
@sugar{1/4%teaspoon} (½ tsp for 4 servings), and a squeeze of lemon juice.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Place chickpeas in a #large bowl{} and mash with a #potato masher{} or #fork{}
until about half the chickpeas are smooth (leave some larger chickpea pieces for
texture).

Stir in scallion greens, mayonnaise mixture, as much dill as you like, and a squeeze
of lemon juice to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide lettuce leaves between #plates{}; fill with chickpea salad. Garnish with
@sliced almonds{1/2%ounce} and serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.